                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12723062" author="dagw" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2009 13:45:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Uploading a patch for this, which makes the hard upgrade use another database,&lt;br/&gt;
by wrapping the offending test cases in a singleUseDatabaseDecorator.&lt;br/&gt;
I manually tested this by creating a system/wombat with a 10.4 release and&lt;br/&gt;
then ran the test against trunk (with derby.database.allowPreReleaseUpgrade=true)&lt;br/&gt;
and verified that after the run, I could still connect to system/wombat with a 10.4 Derby.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running full regressions now. Ready for review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12723566" author="dagw" created="Wed, 24 Jun 2009 14:55:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the output of a run of trunk with this patch of suites.All against a 10.5 &quot;system/wombat&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
As far as I can see the errors and failures are to b expected, falling into two groups:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the new XPLAIN functionality&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Schema name SYSIBM replaced with SYSCS_UTIL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;After the run I could still connect to system/wombat with the 10.5 Derby so it has not been hard upgraded in the run.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12724110" author="dagw" created="Thu, 25 Jun 2009 15:45:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed on trunk as svn 788369. Not resolving yet, since I intend to backport this to the 10.5 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12724116" author="dagw" created="Thu, 25 Jun 2009 16:05:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Back-ported fix to 10.5 as svn 788377, resolving.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12726291" author="kmarsden" created="Thu, 2 Jul 2009 02:12:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;backported to 10.4 and 10.3. Thanks Dag for the fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
